    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In printing and print-making, the individual example produced by the printing of a block, plate, or type, etc., on a sheet of paper. Use when emphasizing the individual instance of printing. For printed images more generally, use "prints."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000050615/IFLA Glossary for Art Librarians (1984)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Úsese cuando se enfatiza la imagen individual al producir una instancia única de impresión. Para imágenes impresas y de manera más general, use "estampa".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
